The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with abstract meaning representations (AMRs), which are a type of semantic representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a neural parser and uses the variational auto-encoding framework, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with graph prediction, which is a topic that falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses a continuous relaxation of the discrete alignments, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
